OL,7,FShe said: "A lot of the stories that
OL,8,Fwe hold in our collections are really
OL,9,Fnegative portrayals of disability.
OL,11,F"They're often stereotyped, they're
OL,12,Fvery institutionalised records, often
OL,13,Fthey're official records, so they tell
OL,14,Fa very negative medicalised story. So,
OL,15,Fit's great to give people a chance to
OL,16,Ftell their own stories in their own
OL,17,Fwords and have those added to our
OL,18,Fcollection."
